main event: Sighting of a luminous, reddish-tinge to bluish-white object that moved from 5 to 90 degrees in 15 minutes over Sulpher Grove, Oldtown, Ohio on March 28, 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared brightly and was luminous.
The witness was vague about the object's motion.
Another witness thought it was a star and said the 30 ft drop could have been an illusion.
The report includes details about four groups of UFO sightings in the Sulpher Grove and Oldtown areas.
No photographs were included in the report.
